+{"id":"frankenpandas-vc9cp","title":"fd90.162: README random sampling example calls non-existent compute_weight(i) — replace with inline expression","description":"fd90.74-161 self-review. The Random Sampling example at line 1641 (added by fd90.115) has:\n\n  let weights: Vec<f64> = (0..df.len()).map(|i| compute_weight(i)).collect();\n\nThe compute_weight function doesn't exist anywhere — it was a placeholder for 'user-defined weight function'. A user copy-pasting this hits:\n  error[E0425]: cannot find function  in this scope\n\nThis is an outlier among the README's code examples — most others compile. Fix: replace with an inline weight expression (e.g. positional weighting where row index becomes the weight) so the example is genuinely runnable. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T15:49:30.931231782Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T15:50:47.796752498Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T15:50:47.793932948Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankenpandas-vhq2","title":"fd90.20: SqlConnection::list_tables for backend-agnostic table discovery","description":"Add SqlConnection::list_tables(schema: Option<&str>) -> Vec<String> trait method for backend-agnostic table discovery. Default impl returns empty Vec (backends that can't introspect). rusqlite impl uses 'SELECT name FROM sqlite_master WHERE type=table' filtered by schema (silently ignored on SQLite per supports_schemas==false). Free-fn list_sql_tables(conn, schema) wrapper exposes the API at fp-io top level. Tests cover empty DB, populated DB, schema-Some on SQLite (silently ignored), schema-Some on a multi-schema stub backend.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:10.294844156Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:24:29.991628127Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:24:29.989102037Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fd90","review","sql"]}
